Overview:
---------
This dataset was made by DBDC3 Task Organizers based on Stanford
Question Answering Dataset (SQuAD) [1].  The data can be used for
both profit and nonprofit purposes under the CC BY-SA 4.0 license
(see LICENSE.txt). The data contain short paragraphs used
as context for DBDC3. Main data are distributed at the following
URL: https://dbd-challenge.github.io/dbdc3/data/DBDC3.zip
For more details of the dataset, refer to [2].

Folder Structure:
-----------------
dbdc3
└── en
    ├── dev
    │   └── CIC_115
    └── eval
        └── CIC_50

Reference:
----------
Please refer to one or both of the following papers when you publish
your results using this dataset.

[1] https://rajpurkar.github.io/SQuAD-explorer/

[2] R. Higashinaka, K. Funakoshi, M. Inaba, Y. Tsunomori, T. Takahashi,
  and N. Kaji, "Overview of dialogue breakdown detection challenge 3,"
  in Proceedings of Dialog System Technology Challenge 6 (DSTC6)
  Workshop, 2017.

